"v.嘲笑 【英】 v. 嘲笑(mock; taunt; scoff at) 【考】 jeer : derision / reprimand: censure(嘲笑的动作表示嘲笑 /谴责的语言表示谴责) 【例】 jeer at sb. for being a sluggard v. (大声)嘲笑; 讥讽 = taunt; n 讥笑的言语 【记】jeer中间有两个嘲笑的眼睛 ee. 【类】jeer: derision = reprimand: censure嘲笑的动作表示嘲笑 = 谴责的语言表示谴责 【记】音：讥尔，讥笑尔，你；音：挤眼耳，嘲笑时总是挤眉弄眼搔耳 jeer (v.)  1550s, gyr, ""to deride, to mock,"" of uncertain origin; perhaps from Dutch gieren ""to cry or roar,"" or German scheren ""to plague, vex,"" literally ""to shear."" OED finds the suggestion that it is an ironical use of cheer ""plausible and phonetically feasible, ... but ... beyond existing evidence."" Related: Jeered; jeering. jeer (n.)  1620s, from jeer (v.)."
